        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">If the fear pathing is clean, your pet will provide a good safety net and free damage. Lots of times, the pet will save you by drawing aggro if your darkness gets resisted, and the like. With a pet, you can also take on more than one mob at a time, if you so desire. Root dotting has never been my particular style, but it does have its place in the bag of necro tricks. If you are comfortable with the risk level of root dotting in your chosen spot, there is nothing wrong with it by any means.</P><P><BR>Cholly<BR>Defiler of the Rathe<BR>BotS<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
