        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"><BR>Use the pet, even post 50 i use my pet when everyone is root dotting. I have my reasons, first off, your pet's mana cost is about 1.5x your mana cost for your best dot, BUT the pet does infinite dmg, and keeps the mob off you. Usually, i would fear snare it, let one dot on it, and then when it broke let the pet solo it, usually by then the 30 seconds of pets free dmg and the dot will have it so licked the pet will just drop it for you. </P><P>There's many other strategies, but im under the opinion that root dotting plain old sucks, root is the equation of fear, in terms of mana and recasts, you're still snaring, you're still dotting, why not through jibaber in the equation, as a form of manafree dmg and safety?</P><P>BTW the whole exp stealing thing is nothing to worry about, if you balance out using your pet and casting dots, you can solo with no downtime at all, thus EASILY outleveling the root dotter who gets ALL the exp, or so says some, i begin to wonder if its really true these days.</P><P><i>The banning of Potus</i><BR><img src="http://members.spree.com/sip1/farkenb/pocrates.jpg"" border=0><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
